### 1. Service Status prüfen
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/status
Accept: application/json

### 2. Hardware Inventar abrufen
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/hardware
Accept: application/json

### 3. Software Inventar abrufen
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/software
Accept: application/json

### 4. Komplettes Inventar abrufen
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/full
Accept: application/json

### 5. Tests mit verschiedenen IP-Adressen
### Lokaler Test
GET http://127.0.0.1api/inventar/status
Accept: application/json

### Netzwerk Test (Beispiel IP - anpassen nach Bedarf)
GET http://192.168.1.100/api/inventar/status
Accept: application/json

### 6. Test mit Custom Headers
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/full
Accept: application/json
User-Agent: InventarClient/1.0
X-Request-ID: test-{{$timestamp}}

### 7. Test der Swagger Dokumentation
GET http://localhost/swagger/index.html
Accept: text/html

### 8. Gesundheitscheck (falls vorhanden)
GET http://localhost/health
Accept: application/json

### 9. API Dokumentation
GET http://localhost/swagger/v1/swagger.json
Accept: application/json

### 10. Performance Test - Mehrere Anfragen
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/hardware
Accept: application/json

###
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/software
Accept: application/json

###
GET http://localhost/api/inventar/status
Accept: application/json

### Variablen für verschiedene Umgebungen
@baseUrl = http://localhost
@remoteUrl = http://192.168.1.100

### Test mit Variablen
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/inventar/full
Accept: application/json

### Remote Test mit Variablen
GET {{remoteUrl}}/api/inventar/status
Accept: application/json
